NAME
       Tcl_GetHostName - get the name of the local host

SYNOPSIS
       #include <tcl.h>

       char *
       Tcl_GetHostName()


DESCRIPTION
       Tcl_GetHostName is a utility procedure used by some of the
       Tcl commands.  It returns a pointer to a string containing
       the  name  for  the current machine, or an empty string if
       the name cannot be determined.  The string  is  statically
       allocated, and the caller must not modify of free it.


